name: Zoë Ames
desc: Zoe realized her passion for coding while completing her masters degree in physics. As a trained physicist, Zoe has a rich background in programming and analytical problem solving. Most comfortable in JavaScript, Zoe is a full stack developer with additional experience using Python. Zoe really enjoys working with Node and Angular to develop cool apps that people can use every day!

name: Mikey Badr
desc: Mikey is biology major turned aspiring developer who mainly speaks Javascript. He is comfortable on the front-end working with Angular and html/css preprocessors, or on the back-end working with Node and Hapi/express. When he isn't coding he can be found playing board games, riding his bike, playing ultimate, rock climbing, watching weird movies, and generally looking for new experiences.

name: Adam Barnhard
desc: Adam Barnhard is a backend web developer experienced in JavaScript development using multiple Node frameworks including Express and Hapi. He graduated from the Nashville Software School in January 2015 and has a bachelors of science in finance from The University of Kansas.

name: David Boling
desc: As a technology aficionado, David is a Full Stack web developer with experience in JavaScript, Node, Angular, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, and more. In his spare time, he strives to learn new programming paradigms, is ever increasing his technological skill set, and loves to compose music as a hobby.

name: Melanie Fryman
desc: Melanie is a full stack web developer with experience in JavaScript, Angular, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, and many other frameworks. She is not ashamed of her love for all things data, gets giddy at the thought of graphs and statistics, and enjoys new challenges. Having worked as an education program evaluator for the past three years, Melanie looks forward to incorporating her programming and analytic skills in the never-ending quest for (practical) science! Melanie holds a masters degree in sociology from Middle Tennessee State University.

name: Brian C Hiatt
desc: I eat tuples of cereal for breakfast and write code in my sleep.

name: Kayla Jones
desc: Kayla has taken her abilities as a visual artist and applied them to Web Design and Development. As primarily a Front-end Developer, she loves to create beautiful digital experiences that merge functionality and design.

name: Matt Keef
desc: Matt, a former chef, has traded his knife kit with a laptop and is now cooking up some hot code!  He has training as a full stack developer and experience with several different technologies.  He enjoys writing code for both client and server, but Matt's greatest passion lies in game development and hopes to turn his passion into a career.

name: Sarah Pearson
desc: Sarah Pearson is a music business professional turned developer and designer with a passion for front-end development and making applications that are smart, intuitive and easy to maneuver.

name: Joy Pratt
desc: Joy has a background in healthcare with over ten years experience as a radiologic technologist. She has worked extensively with mammography data and statistics. She is excited about using her programming skills to explore new opportunities in the tech world.

name: Logan Richardson
desc: Before Nashville Software School, Logan was a lead singer for a rock band that traveled and performed all over the midwest and a Vintage Aircooled Volkswagen mechanic/enthusiast. When he finally lost interest in jumping from sales jobs to mechanics jobs to support his music habit, Logan decided to turn focus toward his technology addiction in order to pursue his teenage ambition to become a sofware developer. He hopes to use and further his skills in development for front-end and back-end code. As long as he is working with technology, he will be more than satisfied.

name: Daniel Roden
desc: Daniel is a coder and designer with a background in neuroscience and fine art.

name: Juan Job Rodriguez
desc: I am software engineer and web developer.

name: Shruti Sharma
desc: Developer, Data Enthusiast, Scientist seeking to build applications that impact lives.

name: Dennis Stanley
desc: While in Nashville software school, Dennis has gained experience in: JavaScript, Node, Angular, Hapi, Express, MongoDB, and many other technologies. His previous education consists of studying advertising and art, where he received a bachelors of science in advertising from Middle Tennessee State University. He’s passionate about continuing to build on the knowledge he has gained at NSS, with his interest leaning more towards the frontend.

name: Nathan Vasquez
desc: Multi-instrumentalist turned coder, Nathan's new kick is making a name for himself in the local tech community!
